PLACEHOLDER — not the real Shortcut binary.

A published iOS Shortcut is a SIGNED Apple property-list (.plist/aea) bundle. It cannot be
authored, signed, or generated from this repository — it must be exported from the Shortcuts
app on Apple hardware (iPhone, iPad, or Mac) by an account that has signed in to iCloud.

To replace this placeholder with the real file (one-time, by Chase):

  1. Build the "Pocket Capture" Shortcut per docs/pocket-capture/ios-shortcut/README.md
     ("Authoring the Shortcut").
  2. Publish it: Share → Copy iCloud Link → paste that URL into INSTALL.md + README.md +
     onboarding (replace ICLOUD_GALLERY_URL_PLACEHOLDER).
  3. Export the binary: Shortcuts → File → Export → save as pocket-capture.shortcut, and
     commit it over this placeholder so the repo carries a reference copy.

The Shortcut's behavior is fully specified in README.md ("What the Shortcut does"):
dictate text → POST https://aipocketagent.com/api/capture/shortcut with
Authorization: Bearer <pca_ token> and JSON body { "text": "...", "source_hint": "siri" }
→ show a "Saved to your brain" notification.
